<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-10-24T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-10-24T03:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/65: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-24T16:00:00+08:00">October 24, 1934—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 24—2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>485. Legation’s 484, October 24, 1 p.m. Chase reports that the Monopoly
                            Bureau has requested Chinese agents of the Standard-Vacuum Company to
                            send delegates to a meeting to be held at Hsinking on the 26th for the
                            purpose of selecting distributors of monopoly kerosene; that company
                            have suggested to agents that the Bureau be informed that the matter
                            should be taken up directly with the company.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
